  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen using `quarkus.config.locations` quarkus swallows errors when the listed URLs cannot be opened.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nQuarkus should use the Fail Early paradigm and fail to start, throwing a clear error that states which given configuration location could not be found.\r\nOptionally another config option could be added to enable ignoring failed config lookups, but this should not be the default.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nQuarkus starts as if all is well and silently ignores the error that happend when trying to read the configuration.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\nRun any quarkus application like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\njava -Dquarkus.config.locations=https://example.com/clearly-wrong.properties -jar target\\greeting-service-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-runner.jar\r\n```\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n_No response_\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.13.5.Final-redhat-00002\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
